Minister of Industry, Trade and Investment, Mr Adeniyi Adebayo has disclosed that the Federal government is set to establish agricultural processing zones in each Senatorial district across the country.  The Minister whodisclosed this at a journalist briefing after  FEC in Abuja said government is working to ensure that it provides credit to investors, through the Bank of Industry (BOI). He said ten million medium and small-scale enterprises would benefit from the proposed credit scheme adding that the government intends to raise $500 million from the African Development Bank for technological innovation in the country.  In another development, the Minister of Water Resources, Mr Suleiman Adamu however revealed that the Council approved contracts for the completion of inherited and abandoned water projects, as well as variation for Tada Shonga Irrigation Project, in Shonga Kwara State.